        <h3 style="margin-top:0; color: var(--goku-blue); font-size: 2rem;">The Heat of Life</h3>
        <div class="reading-text" id="read-ch1b">It is easy to think of chemical reactions as things that only happen in laboratories with bubbling flasks. But the most important exothermic reaction on Earth is happening inside your cells right now. When you eat food, your body breaks it down into a simple sugar called glucose. When you breathe in, oxygen travels to your cells and reacts with this glucose. This reaction, called respiration, slowly and safely releases the trapped energy, powering your muscles, your brain, and keeping your body warm. Without this continuous, microscopic chemical fire, human life would instantly cease to exist.</div>
