        <h3 style="margin-top:0; color: var(--goku-blue); font-size: 2rem;">The Philosophy of Balancing</h3>
        <div class="reading-text" id="read-ch1a">In the late 18th century, a French chemist named Antoine Lavoisier carefully weighed substances before and after a chemical reaction. To his amazement, he discovered that no matter how violently a substance burned, the total mass of the sealed container never changed. This ground-breaking discovery became the Law of Conservation of Mass. It states that matter can neither be created nor destroyed in a chemical reaction. This is the exact reason why we must balance chemical equations today. Every single atom of hydrogen, oxygen, or iron that enters a reaction as a reactant must be accounted for as a product. The universe never loses a single atom; it merely rearranges them into new substances.</div>
