<div class="slide"><div class="content-box">
                <h2>Decomposition Specifics (3 Marks) <span class="pyq-tag">PSEB 2018, 2021, 2023</span></h2>
                <p>Because decomposition reactions require energy to break bonds, they are always <strong>Endothermic</strong>. The energy comes in three forms:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Thermal (Heat):</strong> Heating limestone.<br><span class="equation">CaCO₃(s) + Heat &rarr; CaO(s) + CO₂(g)</span></li>
                    <li><strong>Electrolytic (Electricity):</strong> Splitting water.<br><span class="equation">2H₂O(l) + Electricity &rarr; 2H₂(g) + O₂(g)</span></li>
                    <li><strong>Photolytic (Light):</strong> Used in black & white photography.<br><span class="equation">2AgCl(s) + Sunlight &rarr; 2Ag(s) + Cl₂(g)</span></li>
                </ul>
