<div class="slide"><div class="content-box">
                <h2>Anodizing Aluminum</h2>
                <p>Aluminum is a highly reactive metal, but it is highly resistant to corrosion. Why?</p>
                <p>When exposed to air, it naturally forms a thin oxide layer ($Al_2O_3$). This layer protects the metal underneath from further reaction.</p>
                <div class="template-box">
                    <h3>📋 What is Anodizing?</h3>
