                <p><strong>3. Washing Soda ($Na_2CO_3 \cdot 10H_2O$):</strong> Recrystallization of sodium carbonate gives washing soda.</p>
                <div class="equation">Na₂CO₃ + 10H₂O &rarr; Na₂CO₃·10H₂O</div>
                <p><em>Uses: Glass/soap/paper industries, removing permanent hardness of water.</em></p>
                
                <p><strong>4. Plaster of Paris ($CaSO_4 \cdot rac{1}{2}H_2O$):</strong> Heating Gypsum at exactly 373K.</p>
                <div class="equation">CaSO₄·2H₂O + Heat(373K) &rarr; CaSO₄·&frac12;H₂O + 1&frac12;H₂O</div>
                <p><em>Uses: Doctors use it to support fractured bones.</em></p>
