<div class="slide"><div class="content-box">
                <h2>Extraction Deep Dive</h2>
                <h3>The Thermit Reaction <span class="punjabi">(ਥਰਮਿਟ ਕਿਰਿਆ)</span></h3>
                <p>Highly exothermic displacement reaction. Iron(III) oxide + Aluminum makes molten iron. Used to join railway tracks!</p>
                <div class="equation">Fe₂O₃ + 2Al &rarr; 2Fe(liquid) + Al₂O₃ + Heat</div>
                <h3>Electrolytic Refining <span class="punjabi">(ਬਿਜਲਈ ਸੋਧਣ)</span></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Anode (+):</strong> Impure copper block.</li>
                    <li><strong>Cathode (-):</strong> Pure copper strip. Pure metal deposits here!</li>
                    <li><strong>Anode Mud:</strong> Insoluble impurities that settle at the bottom of the anode.</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="pitfall-box">
                    <h3>🚨 Board Exam Pitfall</h3>
                    <p>Do not reverse Anode and Cathode! Remember: The pure metal is collected at the negative terminal (Cathode).</p>
