                <h2>Rusting & Alloys <span class="punjabi">(ਜੰਗ ਲੱਗਣਾ)</span></h2>
                <p>Iron needs both <strong>Oxygen + Water</strong> to rust.</p>
                <p>We prevent it by painting, oiling, or <strong>Galvanisation <span class="punjabi">(ਗੈਲਵੈਨੀਕਰਨ)</span></strong> - coating steel/iron with a thin layer of Zinc.</p>
                
                <h3>Alloys <span class="punjabi">(ਮਿਸ਼ਰਤ ਧਾਤਾਂ)</span></h3>
                <p>A homogeneous mixture of two or more metals. It improves properties (e.g., pure iron is too soft; adding carbon makes it hard steel).</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Brass:</strong> Copper + Zinc</li>
                    <li><strong>Bronze:</strong> Copper + Tin</li>
                    <li><strong>Solder:</strong> Lead + Tin (low melting point for welding wires)</li>
                    <li><strong>Amalgam:</strong> Any alloy where one of the metals is Mercury ($Hg$).</li>
                </ul>
