<div class="slide"><div class="content-box">
                <h2>Modern Periodic Table Organization</h2>
                <p>Based on <span class="accent">Atomic Number</span> <span class="punjabi">(ਪਰਮਾਣੂ ਸੰਖਿਆ)</span>.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Groups (↓):</strong> 18 vertical columns. Elements in a group have the same number of <em>valence electrons</em>, hence similar chemical properties.</li>
                    <li><strong>Periods (→):</strong> 7 horizontal rows. Elements in a period have the same number of <em>electron shells</em>.</li>
                    <li><span class="accent">The Zig-Zag Line:</span> Separates Metals (left side) from Non-metals (right side). The elements on the line are Metalloids (e.g., Silicon, Boron, Germanium).</li>
                </ul>
